title: MarketWatch First Take: Are any tech companies immune to the economic damage from coronavirus?
text: Now that social-media companies, once the darlings of Wall Street, are confirming lower ad revenue due to the COVID-19 outbreak, investors are wondering if any companies in tech are immune from the pandemic’s economic damage.

title: Facebook, Messenger And WhatsApp Use Soars While Advertising Declines In Pandemic Hit Countries
text: Benzinga is covering every angle of how the coronavirus affects the financial world.

title: Facebook, Microsoft partner with WHO for coronavirus hackathon
text: The World Health Organization has partnered with Facebook, Microsoft and several other tech companies for a hackathon to promote the development of software to take on challenges related to the coronavirus pandemic.

title: Facebook says ad business weakening as traffic spikes amid COVID-19 pandemic
text: Facebook Inc. FB, +8.70% said late Tuesday that its business was being "adversely affected" by the COVID-19 pandemic as traffic has spiked and ad revenue has "weakened.

title: Facebook sees weakening in its ads business due to the coronavirus
text: CNBC's Julia Boorstin reports that Facebook sees weakening in its ads business due to the coronavirus.

title: Facebook says it's seeing weakening in ads business in countries hit by COVID-19
text: Despite an increase in engagement on its some of its platforms "in places hit hardest by the virus," Facebook says it's seeing a weakening in its ads business in countries taking actions to reduce the spread of COVID-19.

title: Facebook Is ‘Just Trying to Keep the Lights On’ as Traffic Soars in Pandemic
text: The social network is straining to deal with skyrocketing usage as its 45,000 employees work from home for the first time.

title: Facebook Rolls Out Paid Leave for Employees Tending to Sick Family Amid Coronavirus
text: Facebook is taking another step to help its workforce of 45,000, offering paid leave of up to 30 days to care for sick family members.

title: Netflix, Facebook to cut data traffic in India to ease network congestion
text: Streaming service Netflix Inc  and social media giant Facebook Inc  said on Tuesday they would reduce the amount of data their services use to ease congested telecoms networks in India, were millions are using home internet amid a lockdown to contain the contravirus outbreak.

title: Facebook eyes multi billion dollar stake in Reliance Jio: FT
text: Facebook Inc  is in talks to buy a multi billion dollar stake in Reliance Industries Ltd's  telecom unit, the Financial Times reported on Tuesday, citing two people with knowledge of the matter.

title: Facebook in talks to acquire stake in top Indian telco Reliance Jio, report says
text: Reliance Jio, a three-and-a-half-year-old subsidiary of India’s most valued firm Reliance Industries, may have attracted the attention of an American giant: Facebook. The social conglomerate is in talks to acquire a 10% stake in Indian telecom operator, the Financial Times reported Tuesday.

title: Social Media Surge Fails to Benefit Facebook and Twitter Stocks
text: Social media stocks have been crushed in recent weeks, even though daily user metrics are skyrocketing.

title: Instagram has a new way for people isolated by coronavirus to connect: sharing posts via video chat
text: Facebook’s Instagram announced a feature that lets users browse the app with friends over video chat.

title: Facebook Knew Audience Metric Was Bogus for Years, Amended Lawsuit Claims
text: New information has emerged in a class action lawsuit against the social media giant.
